","assay-development"],"score":6,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":131,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1330469964},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/EVo7J.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":790,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/790/joy","reputation":224,"display_name":"Joy","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/115/nico","reputation":6011,"display_name":"nico","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":2292,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337238315,"comment_id":3054,"body":"In case you don&#39;t know it, this should be of help: <a href=\"http://www.geneontology.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">geneontology.org<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"score":0,"post_id":2292,"edited":false,"creation_date":1337265501,"comment_id":3063,"body":"i&#39;m afraid a literature crawl is the only reliable way to get domain knowledge like this."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e60c4ebf047734e923ffa4ffa45337cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1122,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1122/rwst","reputation":3115,"display_name":"rwst","accept_rate":100},"score":1,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1345557321,"creation_date":1345557321,"body":"<p>I think your best bet is to blast your transcripts against the <a href=\"http://www.tcdb.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">TCDB<\/a> which has all ion channel templates you can get in the literature. Second best would be to blast against a general protein database