o be organelles rather than a separate species in symbiosis with eukaryotes. Granted, mitochondria and plastids are incapable of living outside their parent cells, and likewise eukaryotes are incapable of surviving without the help of mitochondria and plastids. But this is also true of many other symbiotic pairs in Eukarya. So where does the distinction lie? What makes mitochondria and plastids organelles rather than separate organisms? <\/p>\n","question_id":3167,"tags":["cell-biology","mitochondria","eukaryotic-cells"],"score":8,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":732,"up_vote_count":8,"last_edit_date":1344952207},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/defd0a24bbf93ad6ec98d57bda71633e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1240,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1240/chanelle-ractliffe","reputation":16,"display_name":"Chanelle Ractliffe"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef6c1e9a540c28587fe777f9bcf907af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1231,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1231/mcm","reputation":7783,"display_name":"MCM"},"score":0,"post_id":3230,"edited":false,"creation_date":1345336278,"comment_id":4820,"body":"Can you be any more specific? Sleep affects every single organ and organ system in the body, and everything from hormone levels to cytokine levels change from tissue to tissue based on the amount of sleep you get.   Your question is almost impossible to answer concisely."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/15894a0d103ab92a2cd3b1000efca418?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6422,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6422/cornelius","reputation":6008,"display_name":"Cornelius"},"score":0,"post_id":3230,"edited":false,"creation_date":1406639282,"comment_id":29976,"body":"Similar: <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/q/3028/6422\">biology.stackexcha