ion times, and links to depression and suicide.<\/p>\n","answer_id":3074,"question_id":2707,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2707/examples-of-intracellular-parasites-of-medical-or-economic-importance","last_activity_date":1343781097,"creation_date":1340189649,"answer_count":1,"title":"Examples of intracellular parasites of medical or economic importance?","body":"<p>What are examples of intracellular parasites of medical or economic importance? I have read that <em>Xanthomonas oryzae<\/em> is an intracellular parasite in rice that produces proteins able to cause changes in the gene regulation of the rice cells in order to feed off the sugars produced by the rice cells.<\/p>\n\n<p>I would like to know of other examples of intracellular parasites of medical or economic importance that would be potentially (even if not tested) able to interact with the host's genome in a similar manner.<\/p>\n","question_id":2707,"tags":["genomes","parasitology"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":3074,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":1469,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1340197470},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c97bba51cc8f938dcc806703fb55efc2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":673,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/673/zeller","reputation":384,"display_name":"zeller","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/222b478bab6d59dc5de514a87dba88cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":389,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/389/bobthejoe","reputation":4911,"display_name":"bobthejoe","accept_rate":53},"score":1,"post_id":3049,"edited":false,"creation_date":1343637169,"comment_id":4491,"body":"Question sounds appropriate. I suggest reading <a href=\"http://www.quora.com/Drugs-and-Pharmaceuticals/What-does-it-mean-for-a-medicine-to-have-an-expiration-date\" rel=\"nofollow\">quora.com/Drugs-and-Ph